[1] Uganda (Diarrhea)
Date: Fri, 16 Apr 2004 19:19:21 -0400
From: Alfonso Rodriguez <arodriguezm@SaludFMV.org>
Source: AllAfrica.com / New Vision news (Kampala) [edited]
<http://allafrica.com/stories/200404160459.html>

KCC Braces for Cholera
--------------------------
Kampala city health authorities are bracing for a possible cholera epidemic
following reported deaths and hospital cases recently. The city director
of health services, Dr. Mesak Mubiru, on 15 Apr 2004, said 2 people aged 28
and 50, of Kanyogoga Zone, Namuwongo in Makindye Division, died of
diarrhea-related illness.
Mubiru said 5 people had been treated in Mulago Hospital for diarrhea and
vomiting. He, however, said it was too early to conclude that the disease
was cholera, saying they were still conducting tests at the Central
Laboratory Services, Wandegeya.
The Makindye Division health inspector, Joseph Tirango said the area had
poor sanitation and that it lacked safe drinking water. "These people do
not have toilets. They dispose of the feces anywhere. The sanitation is
very poor," he said. He said there was only 1 KCC-owned communal latrine,
accessed at a fee.
The division senior assistant town clerk Grace Tabuzibwa said they had
requested KCC to allow residents use the latrine for free. Tabuzibwa said
they were intensifying public health education programs to combat any
possible cholera outbreak.
