[5] Zambia (Gastroenteritis)
Date: Mon, 12 Apr 2004 19:21:03 -0400
From: Alfonso Rodriguez <arodriguezm@SaludFMV.org>
Source: All Africa.com / The Times of Zambia [edited]
<http://allafrica.com/stories/200404120539.html>

CBoH Arrests Bweengwa Diarrhea Outbreak
-------------------------------------------------
The Central Board of Health (CBoH) says a diarrhea outbreak in Bweengwa
constituency southern province that claimed 6 lives has been brought under
control.
CBoH spokesperson Dr Victor Mukonka said in an interview in Lusaka
yesterday that investigations had shown that the outbreak was just an
ordinary diarrhea and not cholera as earlier suspected. He said the
remaining 12 patients who were admitted at the health center had all been
discharged.
6 villagers last week [1st week of April 2004] died in Monze after drinking
contaminated water, while 12 others were admitted at Bweengwa rural health
center the villagers complained of diarrhea and vomiting.
UPND Bweengwa member of Parliament (MP) Japhet Moonde alleged that the
water was contaminated as a result of the poor sanitary conditions caused
by the rains.
